3/3

Overall, my judgement was fairly good. 

Of the non-minted but bullish projects, most were still interesting to me but had no momentum. 

I should have listed to myself better and sold what I wasn't bullish on pre-mint. Holding 3 of those which isn't great

2/3

For each mint, I marked "bullishness" on a 5-pt scale (1=Avoid, 5=Bullish)

Of the 58 WLs 
- 21 (36%) were a 4 or 5
- 6 I did not end up minting, 15 I did mint
- All 6 of the "happy to hold" projects were a 4+
- Only 5 minted projects were a 2, 0 projects minted at 1 (Avoid)

I have been tracking my WLs over the past 5 weeks. Some quick stats:

- 58 total Whitelists
- 26 of those that I minted
- 13 of them I still own
- 6 of them I am happy about still owning
